        "title": "Calling generic method by passing parameters?",
        "body": "<p>I have below Generic method.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class MyClass\n{\n    public &lt;T extends MyObject&gt; T  getResult(Class&lt;T&gt; class, String id){\n\n      //Have some logic\n\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>As it is a generic method what kind of parameters do i need to pass?<\/p>\n\n<p>I mean which parameters do i need to pass to the method?<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks!<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 20418544,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "generics"
        ],
