            "creation_date": 1386315537,
            "body": "<p>You need some class extending MyObject:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class A extends MyObject { ... }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>If you have this, you can call the method like so:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>A a = myClass.getResult(A.class, \"id\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You get an instance of A  back.<\/p>\n\n<p>You may also skip creating class A and use MyObject directly, since the constraint <code>&lt;T extends MyObject&gt;<\/code> makes <code>T<\/code> match every class that extends MyObject, including the class MyObject itself.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418594,
            "question_id": 20418544,
            "last_edit_date": 1386315855
        },
        {
            "owner": {
